In this development notebook I'm going to try trimming the alignment using Gappyout and see if I can get it working, as it might speed up the tree-building process.

Sativa¶

Sativa does a number of useful things, including checking the reference database for putatively mis-labelled sequences. We have run it in another notebook on the positives database (which is small) and now need to do the same on the main reference database (which is not!).

To avoid confusion, let's navigate to a new sub-directory

In [1]:
cd /home/working/AgainstRefDB/Curat1/FINAL/Sativa/

/home/working/AgainstRefDB/Curat1/FINAL/Sativa

We already have downloaded the relevant .gb file, let's copy it to this location...

In [2]:
cp ../eyorks_flora_curated.gb .
In [3]:
ls

955081477588150.11_rbcL.fasta     rbcL_cropped_eyorks.fa
align_eyorks.pkl                  rbcL_cropped_eyorks.gb
eyorks_flora_curated.gb           rbcL_eyorks_id-1.uc
loci_counts.txt                   rbcL_nr_pre_Sativa_eyorks.gb
loci.csv                          remove.txt
nr_eyorks.pkl                     Sativa_final.ipynb
raw_eyorks.pkl                    Sativa_preandpost_final.ipynb
rbcL_clustered_cleaned_eyorks.fa  species_vs_locus_raw.csv
rbcL_clustered_cleaned_eyorks.gb  target_locus_eyorks.csv

def crop_to_CDS(record):
    """The function crops a Genbank record to only retain the sequnence of the first CDS"""
    
    from Bio import SeqFeature
    
    strands=[]
    r = record
    print "\nprocessing record: '%s' " %r.id,
    if r.features:
        for feature in r.features:
            if feature.type == 'CDS':
                strands.append(feature.location.strand)
                qualifiers = feature.qualifiers
                
                if 'gene' in qualifiers:
                    gene_name = feature.qualifiers['gene'][0]
                    r.seq = r.seq[feature.location.start:feature.location.end]
                    feature.location = SeqFeature.FeatureLocation(SeqFeature.ExactPosition(0), 
                                                                  SeqFeature.ExactPosition(feature.location.end - feature.location.start), 
                                                                 1)
                    break
                elif 'product' in qualifiers:
                    gene_name = feature.qualifiers['product'][0]
                    r.seq = r.seq[feature.location.start:feature.location.end]
                    feature.location = SeqFeature.FeatureLocation(SeqFeature.ExactPosition(0),
                                                                  SeqFeature.ExactPosition(feature.location.end - feature.location.start),
                                                                 1)
                
        for feature in r.features:
            if feature.type == 'source':
                strands.append(feature.location.strand)
                feature.qualifiers['note'] = ['modified from original record: cropped to only CDS of '+gene_name]
                feature.location = SeqFeature.FeatureLocation(SeqFeature.ExactPosition(0), 
                                                              SeqFeature.ExactPosition(len(r.seq)), 
                                                             feature.location.strand)
                break
                    
        if len(list(set(strands))) > 1:
            r.seq = r.seq.reverse_complement()
            print "\t.. reverse complementing",

        print "\t.. final length: %s" %len(r.seq),

    else:
        print "\t  no features found .."
        
           

    #print r.format('genbank')

N.B. Some accession numbers on the blacklist may have already been removed at an earlier stage in the process - the script will report how many it tries to remove, and how many it actually does.

from Bio import SeqIO
from Bio import SeqFeature

ids=[]
temp=[]
blacklist=[]
tooshort=[]
strands=[]
accessions = open('../AccessionBlacklist.txt','r')
dropped=0
droppedlength=0

for line in accessions:
    ids.append(line.strip())
    

recs_to_keep = {'rbcL': []}
recs_to_drop = {'rbcL': ids}

print "Blacklist recs to drop: %s" %recs_to_drop['rbcL']
print "Read in %s records" %len(pj.records)

for r in pj.records:
    if r.features:
        for feature in r.features:
            if feature.type == 'CDS':
                strands.append(feature.location.strand)
                qualifiers = feature.qualifiers
                
                if 'gene' in qualifiers:
                    gene_name = feature.qualifiers['gene'][0]
                    r.seq = r.seq[feature.location.start:feature.location.end]
                    feature.location = SeqFeature.FeatureLocation(SeqFeature.ExactPosition(0), 
                                                                  SeqFeature.ExactPosition(feature.location.end - feature.location.start), 
                                                                 1)
                    break
                elif 'product' in qualifiers:
                    gene_name = feature.qualifiers['product'][0]
                    r.seq = r.seq[feature.location.start:feature.location.end]
                    feature.location = SeqFeature.FeatureLocation(SeqFeature.ExactPosition(0),
                                                                  SeqFeature.ExactPosition(feature.location.end - feature.location.start),
                                                                 1)
      
    if len(r.seq) < 500:
        recs_to_drop['rbcL'].append(r.id)
        droppedlength+=1
        
for r in pj.records:
    if not r.id in recs_to_drop['rbcL']: 
        recs_to_keep['rbcL'].append(r.id)
        temp.append(r)
    
    else:
        print "exclude: %s" %r.id
        dropped+=1
        blacklist.append(r.id)
        
out = open('rbcL_cropped_eyorks.gb', 'w')
SeqIO.write(temp, out, 'genbank')
out.close()

out = open('rbcL_cropped_eyorks.fa', 'w')
SeqIO.write(temp, out, 'fasta')
out.close()

print "Dropped blacklist records: %s (of %s)" %(dropped,len(ids))
print "Of which, dropped records because <500bp: %s" %droppedlength
print "Kept: %s" %len(temp)

del(temp)

ids = []

uc=open('rbcL_eyorks_id-1.uc', 'r')

for line in uc:
    if line.startswith('C'):
        ids.append(line.split("\t")[8])

seqs = []
from Bio import SeqIO
for r in pj.records:
    if r.id in recs_to_keep['rbcL']:
        seqs.append(r)

out = open('rbcL_nr_pre_Sativa_eyorks.gb','w')
SeqIO.write(seqs, out, 'genbank')
out.close()

pj.records_by_locus.keys()

['rbcL']

The alignment tries to take the protein sequences for everything and align these, then back-align the actual base-pair sequences. So we need to remove the (very small) number of poorly-labelled records that will break this.

In [34]:
from Bio import SeqFeature

strands=[]
notranslation=[]
nogene=[]

remove=[]

for r in pj.records:
    
    print "\nprocessing record: '%s' " %r.id,
    if r.features:
        for feature in r.features:
            if feature.type =='CDS':
                qualifiers = feature.qualifiers
                if 'translation' not in qualifiers:
                    print "No translation"
                    notranslation.append(r.id)
                    remove.append(r.id)
                    break
                elif 'gene' not in qualifiers:
                    print "No gene"
                    nogene.append(r.id)
                    remove.append(r.id)
                    break                    

                  
                    
print "\nNumber without translations: %s" %len(notranslation)
print "Bad records: %s" %notranslation

print "Number without gene: %s" %len(nogene)
print "Bad records: %s" %nogene  

out = open('remove.txt', 'w')

for item in remove:
  out.write("%s\n" % item)

out.close()

dropped=0

for line in accessions:
    ids.append(line.strip())
    

recs_to_keep = {'rbcL': []}
recs_to_drop = {'rbcL': ids}

print "Blacklist recs to drop: %s" %recs_to_drop['rbcL']

for r in pj.records:
        
    if not r.id in recs_to_drop['rbcL']: 
        recs_to_keep['rbcL'].append(r.id)
        temp.append(r)
    
    else:
        print "exclude: %s" %r.id
        dropped+=1
        blacklist.append(r.id)
        
out = open('rbcL_clustered_cleaned_eyorks.gb', 'w')
SeqIO.write(temp, out, 'genbank')
out.close()

out = open('rbcL_clustered_cleaned_eyorks.fa', 'w')
SeqIO.write(temp, out, 'fasta')
out.close()


print "Found blacklist records: %s (of %s)" %(dropped,len(recs_to_drop['rbcL']))
print "Kept: %s" %len(temp)

Tree building¶

============================¶

SATIVA post-processing¶

In the meantime we have run SATIVA on the alignment that was the basis of the above tree.

Now we are going to highlight the records that SATIVA considers mislabelled in the tree. We are also going to add a heatmap to the tree illustrating the confidence that SATIVA has in a given call.

Parse SATIVA output and record putatively mislabelled sequence records and the confidence of the call.

In [364]:
rec_mislabelled = {}
sativa=open('rbcL.mis', 'r')

for line in sativa:
    if not line.startswith(";"):
        rec_mislabelled[line.split("\t")[0]] = line.split("\t")[4]

Add two new qualifiers containing info about the SATIVA results to the sequence features.

In [365]:
for r in pj.records:
    if r.id in rec_mislabelled:
        for f in r.features:
            f.qualifiers['mislabeled'] = ['yes']
            f.qualifiers['mislabeled_conf'] = [rec_mislabelled[r.id]]
    else:
        for f in r.features:
            f.qualifiers['mislabeled'] = ['no']
            f.qualifiers['mislabeled_conf'] = [0.0001]
In [366]:
pj.propagate_metadata()
